  "body": "### Description\n\n`TenantConfigResolver` is used to resolve OIDC configurations on the fly, dynamically. However, if the default tenant is not configured, the authentication start up will fail with the connection errors. To solve the problem, users have to disable the default tenant, `quarkus.oidc.tenant-enabled=false`.\r\n\r\nIt should not be required though, as users can spend awhile trying to figure out what is going on\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nDetect that TenantConfigResolver is available, if yes, do not report errors if the default tenant is not configured, disable it automatically",
